gomodel:SYNGO_973  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 2: Proprioceptive sensory neurons that synapse onto motor neurons in the spinal cord receive axo-axonic inputs from GABAergic inhibitory interneurons or GABApre neurons. Loss of NB-2 resulted in a decrease of GABApre boutons onto sensory presynapses.\n\n12/10/2017 Pim\n- The study uses a general Contactin-5/NB-2 KO making the site of action (pre/postsynaptic) unclear. However, in Fig.1 the authors show that Contactin-5/NB-2 is only expressed by proprioceptive sensory neurons and not by motorneurons. The site of action or Contactin-5/NB-2 in synapse organization must therefore be presynaptic. In Fig.2 a positive correlational relationship between level of presynaptic Contactin-5/NB-2 expression and the number of boutons in line with this idea.. Experimental description: \"mouse strains were used in this study\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_973" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

